\newlabel{fig:kak-circuit}{{2.5}{19}{KAK decomposition of a two-qubit unitary: $U = (A_1 \otimes A_2)\,U'\,(B_1 \otimes B_2)$. The local unitaries $A_i$ and $B_i$ require no CNOT gates; only the entangling core $U'$ requires CNOT gates (1--3 depending on the gate).\relax }{figure.caption.12}{}}
